items.name: ComfyUI Extreme detail control Ksampler for SDXL
items.description:
full grid link (142Mo jpeg)

If you appreciate this contribution and would like to support future developments, feel free to check my ko-fi !

Introducing the SDXL-dedicated KSampler Node for ComfyUI

Hello ComfyUI enthusiasts,

I am thrilled to introduce a brand-new custom node for our beloved interface, ComfyUI. Designed to handle SDXL, this ksampler node has been meticulously crafted to provide you with an enhanced level of control over image details like never before.

Traditionally, working with SDXL required the use of two separate ksamplers—one for the base model and another for the refiner model. However, with the new custom node, I've combined the functionality of these two ksamplers into a single unit. This node not only manages both the base and the refiner models of SDXL, but it also handles the noise necessary for generating the images.

What does this mean for you? Precision. With this custom node, you can control noise levels with an unprecedented level of detail, leading to more nuanced and compelling outputs. The node is also integrated with a function to rescale the tonemap courtesy of the original developer, comfyanonymous, allowing a higher CFG scale to be used.

To integrate the noise control functionality, I've used functions developed by BlenderNeko. His brilliant work on noise control can be found on his Github page.

This SDXL-dedicated ksampler node is a labor of love, designed to streamline your creative process and elevate your outputs. I believe that tools should work for the user, not the other way around, and this custom node aims to do exactly that.

You can get started with the node on ComfyUI's Github page.

If you appreciate this contribution and would like to support future developments, feel free to visit my Buy Me a Coffee page. Any support goes a long way in fueling my efforts to continue enhancing our creative journey.

Let's continue making ComfyUI even better, together.

To creativity and beyond!

items.name: surtr/スルト/史尔特尔 (Arknights)
items.description:
How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both surtr_arknights.pt and surtr_arknights.safetensors, then use surtr_arknights.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use surtr_arknights.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

それらを同時に使用してください。この場合、surtr_arknights.ptとsurtr_arknights.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。surtr_arknights.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にsurtr_arknights.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

同时使用它们。在这种情况下，您需要下载surtr_arknights.pt和surtr_arknights.safetensors这两个文件，然后将surtr_arknights.pt用作纹理反转嵌入， 同时使用surtr_arknights.safetensors作为LoRA。

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is surtr_arknights, and the recommended tags are masterpiece, best quality, highres, solo, {surtr_arknights:1.10}, red_hair, horns, long_hair, purple_eyes, bangs, breasts, very_long_hair, hair_between_eyes, cleavage, demon_horns, medium_breasts, large_breasts.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Surtr Arknights

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/surtr_arknights, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/surtr_arknights, which may be help to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

items.description:
An offshoot of the dataset of Bigger Girls Model with the addition of custom tags and a more curated selection of data.

Know anything about tagging images? Consider becoming a curator here:

https://discord.gg/mw4nebTUu

Tagging

The underscores are important to keep! It was tagged that way on purpose (to keep the token unique).

The LoRA contains the following artists (more to be added in future versions), divided into high_aesthetic and medium_aesthetic (which are tags):

high_aesthetic:
Akina, BetterWithSalt, c-cu, CoffeeSlice, DrWorm, Ekusupanshon, KipTeiTei, Lazorchef, ryokucha_michi, Sizemologist, Squarewave, Tashoelle

medium_aesthetic:

BreadWithKeptchup, MysteryDad, NewMetrack

The weight of the woman is controlled by the following tags, in order of weight:

skinny, curvy, plump, fat, immobile, fatblob

Hip size (as of v5) are controlled by the following tags:
wide hips, gigantic_hips, hyper_hips

There are also the following custom tags:

hyper_belly, stuffed_belly, belly_bigger_than_body (WIP, not reliable), reddish_belly (WIP), belly_overhang, double_belly

stretchmarks

hose, hose_in_mouth (WIP)

apple_shaped_body, pear_shaped_body, hourglass_figure

feeding (WIP)

stuck, stuck_in_doorway (WIP)

burp (WIP)

double_chin

belly_on_table, belly_on_ground

gurgling_noise (WIP)

In addition to custom tags, the following "standard" danbooru tags are likely helpful:

belly, big belly, hand(s) on own stomach, belly grab, thick thighs, wide hips, covered navel, midriff, midriff peek... (just search tags on danbooru!)

"Stretchmarks" guidance:

You may want to put "cuts, scar, scar on face, facial mark" in the negatives. And play with emphasis of "stretchmarks". If you use ADetailer, put stretchmarks in the negatives (or do not include it in the positive prompt) for the face detailing.

Split hyper_hips into gigantic_hips and hyper_hips. There should now be more control over hips.

items.name: Michael Kirkbride Lora
items.description:
A Lora trained on the concept art drawings Michael Kirkbride did for the Elder Scrolls series as posted on the UESP.

Triggers with michael_kirkbride. It's best at humanoid characters, decent at bugs and monsters, not too good at landscapes and cities.

Most output will be monochrome because the whole dataset was monochrome. Sometimes it's a good idea to force monochrome to get better looking output. Additional helpful tags for that are ink \(medium\), sketch, traditional art and concept art.

I tried to teach it ES races, as well as silt strider. The races work decently well. It is especially good at Dunmer (for obvious reasons). See the X/Y plot for a comparison.

Hi-res fix seems to really mess with the ouput, it makes everything way too clean. I recommend just generating normally and then sending good results to an upscaler as needed.

P.S. Version 1.0 was a sloppily trained Lora for which I did no curating of data or tags. It's less like actual Michael Kirkbride art, but may still provide interesting output.

items.description:
Stephanie 'Steph' Rayner is an Australian fashion model based in LA. She's been on my list for a long time and I think she totally deserves her own TI. :)

130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (stphr4yner:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Geoglyphiks SDXL 1.0 art style lora
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Geoglyphiks art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Geoglyphiks is a visionary artist and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 resolution and is able to produce higher details compared to my 1.5 model.

I use this at a weight of around 0.75 but sometimes I'll have to go down to 0.25 or up to 1.1 depending on the prompt. I used clip skip 1 or 2 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. You can bump the CFG higher than 7 on this one if you want to. I use it between 7 - 15 so feel free to experiment.

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

items.name: ReverseCowgirl
items.description:
Use at .7 and the trigger word is revcow. I was frustrated that there were no really good reverse cowgirl lora's so I decided to make my own. This lora is extracted from a fine-tuned model of PerfectLevel10 model (which is a merge of Level4 and PerfectWorld). I trained with over 700 reverse cowgirl images (768 x 768) and then extracted the lora from the fine-tuned model. The original full model (which is better than the lora) can be found on my profile page. If you are going to use this lora, I highly recommend using PerfectLevel10 (which you can also find on my profile) as your base model for this. If you'd like to support me (or see lots more of my work), check out patreon.com/Virtualbeautiesai .

My workflow is to use this lora along with a lora for a specific character, while working with PerfectLevel10 as my base model. I set the revcow lora to .7 and the one for the character to .75-.85. Usually still need to inpaint the faces and sometimes chests of the characters. Probably get good images about 1/3rd of the time, which is a good rate for sex Loras and some of the images are really outstanding for photorealistic sex images. I'll be doing a series of other sex acts but collecting the images takes a while. Hope you make some great stuff with this.

items.name: Hanako Ikezawa (Katawa Shoujo)
items.description:
Trained on NAI.

V1.5:

Best weight between : 0.75-0.95.

Prompt activator: ikezawa hanako
Major prompt words: burn mark, burn scar, scar, hair over one eye

Outfit prompts:

school uniform: school uniform, black bow, shirt, long sleeves, green skirt
casual outfit: casual outfit, berret, black bowtie, jacket, black pants
nightgown: nightgown

I added images to the dataset and reorganized the prompt words. I think that, perhaps, textual inversions like 'bad hand' reduce burns on the hand. The burns look more similar, even though they still vary somewhat. You can increase their prominence by adjusting the LoRA weight or by using parentheses, for example, '(burn scar:1.1)'. The outfits are a bit more accurate.

In some complex prompts, you may need to add the clothes color. I initially included the color in the prompt to avoid any issues, but you can try removing it to make the prompt lighter if you prefer.

V1.0
Prompt activator:  hanakoikezawa
Major prompt words: hair over one eye, burn
Outfit prompts:

  • school uniform, (green skirt, black tights, black bow, long sleeves)*

  • main outfit, (black hat, blue jacket, black pants)*

  • nightgown

*If the main trigger word does not work properly

Best weight between : 0.7-0.95.

It's hard to have her face burned without using 'hair over one eye.' You can increase the trigger word 'burn' or ask for the face to be specifically burned, but then the entire face will also be affected, not just the right side alone. I am showing two examples in my preview images.

If you have any issues with this LoRA or if you have any suggestions, don't hesitate to communicate them.
